annotation.TEXT: And, as expected, it healed me. Now, as usual, I'll buy the 3 Jellied Yams, but I shouldn't need the midpoint, and I'm definitely not buying the overpriced 1-ups here.
Yeah, that big star definitely came from me, and it's unavoidable too. So, if you use Crash Star, and nothing hits you out of it, you're guaranteed to take a hit anyway.
She also has Ice magic, which I can indeed get by whacking her while she's using it.
And yeah, it's single-use alright, as I no longer have that Crash Star medal now. Man, I bet I could've gotten the flawless if I'd just stuck with Charge Buster.
There's that Crash Star. Do I risk using it? Well, if I'm super-confident that I'll be safe standing still for several seconds, then maybe...
BTW, in case you didn't notice, there's a "whoosh" sound effect when Charge Buster is fully changed.
Alright, it's boss time! Okay, first, I'll ditch Wind, and maybe try to whack Tsubaki with my staff to see what kinds of spells I can get.
Whoa, that's new! Whacking that walking armor produced a spell I haven't seen before!
Ooh, there's Charge Buster already! Okay, don't fall for Koumei's trap this time. Wait until it's safe, then go for it.
Oh, how nice. Just like how abilities are sometimes handed out in some Kirby games starting with Kirby Super Star. (They're called Copy Essences in Kirby games.)
Did that giant star that hurt me come from my usage of it? And was that what happened to the white magician earlier? Argh...
D'oh! Couldn't dodge the ice. I did note that Crash Star does do a lot of damage, so I guess it's sort of a risk/reward thing. Anyway, this battle's nearly over now.
Okay, I got out of that quickly, but I could be in another jam here...
There's a Ball enemy. I wonder how you get up there...
Uh, oh... Ball, protect me!
Nuts. I wanted to see if I could knock that block into her, but she went too high.
Okay, I'm going to ludicrous speed for a moment now.
Super combo! (4 hits)
I wonder how much damage that'll do if I hit Tsubaki with it?
Oh, what the pudding was that?! I couldn't duck under the ice at that height?
And with that, world 2 is completely done! ...Except for 2-1's moon, which I'll come back for later.
Okay, I don't know what happened there. Did he hit himself with his own Crash Star or something? Well, regardless, I got screwed out of my chance to whack him...
Triple combo!
Ooh, what's this? A new feature?
Umm... What...?
Oh, that's funny how I can knock away an ice block with Ball. What if I use Ball on the enemy-spawning cave?
...Air Bound? So, that's what appears when she's whacked when she's about to toss out bunnies.
I could use Ice, but I'd have to get close to her, and Ground Spark is already good for distance attacks. Of course, since she tends to hover, Charge Buster is even better...
Yeah, the moon's nice.
Science count: 1
Yeah, I had done that Crash Star experiment again, since I wasn't sure what footage I'd be keeping at the time.
Okay, let's see how doable this jump is without Ball.
I see something up there.
Okay, I am forbidding myself from using Crash Star, obviously. I'm gonna stick with Ground Spark, unless I'm able to safely get Charge Buster.
But, it doesn't matter, for I have gotten the achievement for the flawless victory anyway!
"I, Garland, shall knock you all down!" ...Wait, that's another game.
--D'oh! Okay, I'm sure I'll need to bounce up and get that Ice right there, so I'll just quickly restart the level.
These guys launch their icy blasts in an arc. Also, I now doubt I needed to bounce up to get Ice like I did there, since I could've just gotten it here.
D'oh! Argh! I can't believe I screwed that up... Okay, you know what? If I have to, I'll replay the level later just to see what spell that guy was wielding.
Just another quick experiment there. The Plum Tea fully healed me when I was at 1 HP, so it's not just a single-heart recovery.
End of the line there.
Oh, boy. What am I dealing with here? Maybe I should equip Ball while riding this platform to guard me from incoming enemies.
Heh. Tobari's like, "Talk to the hand!"
Triple combo!
DOUBLE KILL!
Moon count: 11
OH, WHAT?!?!
The moon's sick? Oh, noes! ...Wait, how can a moon get sick?
Huh, the walking armor disappeared on its own there, before I could take it out with Ground Sparks.
Okay, she's using Crash Star, which is easy to dodge as long as I'm not an idiot. I may be able to finish her off here! (Maybe I should've switched back to Ground Spark here.)
D'oh!
Ooh, lucky me! The flame jets (plural) were both off when I came across! And, thanks to my Ice, they should both be off permanently now.
Wow, that just looked so silly! Okay, so what's in the next room? A moon that requires Ice and Ball?
Alright, time for some science!
Well, maybe with Air Bound, I can keep going without needing the platform.
Okay, first life bar down, and I somehow haven't taken any damage yet! Can I get the flawless victory on my first try?
Hmm... Maybe Ball would be a good idea here, for more speed, although I risk hitting the flame jet on the other side. But, 1 damage is better than a bottomless pit.
Meanwhile, we have a shop and a boss door.
Ooh, Charge Buster! Wait, don't be hasty... This must be Koumei's trap.
Oh, yeah. That definitely doesn't look like a spell I've seen before!
Alright, that ice block was at the perfect height.
Okay, so she tossed out some bunnies, then sent this slow-moving magic circle at me. I probably don't want to let that touch me.
Okay, this guy does indeed give Crash Star. Now, for an experiment...
Whoa, I'm amazed I was able to dodge that.
There it is again... Of course, when I'm able to move, these big stars are easy to dodge.
I like how my player sprite has been jogging in place behind the text boxes during this whole conversation.
But, will I need Air Bound? ...Probably. Ball does add a little bit of height, but not enough to clear this wall.
And, there's nothing to the right, so I'll probably have to approach that from the left.
Hello, and welcome back to Tobari! Now, following that scientific death, I just quit back to the title screen and reloaded my file. Okay, it's time for 2-6!
0 attempts later...
Argh! I was hoping I was invincible while using it, but I guess those fireballs just barely missed me. However, I was unable to move in time to dodge that big star...
Okay, that got me 4 coins, but is there anything more?
DOUBLE KILL! ...Aw, I was sure I whacked her there, so why didn't I get Charge Buster? I'd like to get ahold of that spell if possible...
Yep, there's a line-guided platform. Oh, I should--
I wonder if I can even hit Tsubaki with it at all?
There's stuff up there, but even Ball + Air Bound isn't nearly enough to reach it.
This could've been bad, but it wasn't.
DOUBLE KILL! And, a fully charged shot did I think about as much damage to Tsubaki as that axe hit, but this is much easier to hit with.
Very doable.
Almost forgot to bring up the pause menu description there, and I'm glad I did, because this sounds just like the single-use Crash ability from the Kirby games!
Yep, red spikes are instant death, even if you have 6 hearts. (Also, when you die, you lose any extra heart containers you had.)
Let's see if I can find a safer time to use Crash Star this time.
Oh, my... That looks like a tricky jump. Can Tobari clear a 5-tile wide gap with a jump low enough to get under the skewer? ...Maybe.
Finally scored a hit, and it did moderate damage, but this axe is seriously too slow for my liking, so I think I'm going to discard it now.
Looks like it. Okay, this conversation goes on for a while, so click here to skip most of it.
First life bar down.
A total of 4 attempts later (which I showed all the fails for)...
...knock us all down?
So close...
Yep, and there's the moon! Wow, this moon was way easier and way less scary to get than 2-5's moon! I'm definitely not complaining about that!
Okay, that seriously sounds like Yu-Gi-Oh! "It's time to d-d-d-d... d-d-d-d-duel!"
DOUBLE KILL!
Gotcha! ...Okay, now what? ...I guess I just drop back down and ride the platform.
Platforms, eh?
Also, ice blocks vanish after about 6 seconds, so I can't waste too much time climbing up.
Okay, you can't open blocks with Ice magic. Also, there's a bunch of coins I'm gonna miss most of.
Oh, no... Come back, platform!
Ooh, whacking her while she was charging up the bat summoning caused Charge Buster to appear. I like the sound of that one.
Ooh, Wind. I'll certainly swap out Air Bound for that.
Alright, let's take on the boss! Is it Tsubaki?
Triple combo! Yeah, definitely clear out the rabbits and walking armor as quickly as you can.
And, getting up to the Ball duder from here is easy.
First life bar down.
I don't accidentally want to hit the Wind magician if I can help it.
Hmm... I'm missing a heart from a hit I took, so can I buy the Plum Tea? ...Yes I can.
...Sword? Huh, so that's what appears if I whack her when she's about to deploy the walking armor. Sword is decent, but requires me to be close-range.
Sweet!
Well, let's challenge Tsubaki again.
And, I bet I'll have to combine Air Bound with Ball in order to reach something, so I guess I'll discard Ice.
Well, this is the end of the room, and I think I see what must be done-- I have to freeze one of those white bunnies in midair and use it as a stepping stone to climb up.
I'm surprised I didn't get burned there.
Gotcha! ...Oh, I just realized I never grabbed either heart in the arena to heal the damage I took from the Crash Star experiment before I entered the boss battle.
Yeah, I'm not gonna try ducking under ice at that height this time. Alright, Charge Buster get! Now I can easily attack her even when she's hovering.
Okay, here's another checkpoint + door combo. Now, if I go right from here with Ball + Air Bound, can I reach that ledge I saw before?
DOUBLE KILL!
Whoa. Okay, hitting a spring doesn't automatically refresh my Air Bound usage like landing on solid ground does. I probably should keep this in mind.
Or, maybe I shouldn't, since I have to dodge blocks too, and I could easily lose control.
So, here's what the world 3 map looks like, and I shall begin the Silverburn Desert next time! To be continued... Yo!
Huh, there's a magician wearing white over there. I don't think I've seen that color of magician before. I wonder if that duder's got a brand new spell...
Whoa, whoa, whoa! I want this spell, whatever it is! I think this might be the spell I missed out on from that white magician earlier!
Slammin'!
Oh, man! Special music!
Alright, can I whack that white magician this time?
This is starting to sound like the plot of a Touhou game.
Yep, there's a heart. Okay, time for more ludicrous speed!
Yeah, you definitely don't need to bounce off of those first two enemies to reach Ice early.
How did I not get hit by that fireball? Hitboxes, man!
She can also shoot out fireballs. (I bet I get Fire if I whack her while she's charging that one up.)
Anyway, click here if you want to skip this conversation.
Whoa, there! Well, as much as I like Ground Spark, I'm gonna have to pass on it this time, since I'm sure I'll need this Ball + Air Bound combo.
Oh, like the 30% field power bonus from the first season of the Yu-Gi-Oh! anime?
Yeah, like that, but I don't think that ice block is quite high enough.
D'oh! Whatever. There's a heart coming up soon anyway. So, this time, I'll go ahead and take Ground Spark.
Huh. Ball alone isn't quite enough to get me onto a 6-tile high ledge. Of course, as I showed last time, Air Bound will get me onto 7.
There's that walking armor, but Axe is just too slow for me.
Alright, Tsubaki is beaten, and the only times I got hit were when I was unable to dodge while using Crash Star, so it shouldn't be too hard to get the flawless victory.
So, she can summon bats too. Fortunately, Ball can be used to protect me from them (and the bunnies too).
Alright, I get an achievement for clearing world 2, but... I still want that flawless victory.
Uh, oh...
Okay, I think those circles just slow me down while I'm touching them, so they aren't directly harmful. Still, being slowed down would make it hard to dodge other stuff.
Whoa, careful. Maybe I could've ducked under that, but whatever.
Nothing further to the right. I figured I'd check, just in case there was a 1-up or something hidden in the extreme corner.
Okay, I'm going for it! (Watch her life bar.)
Or, the platform can come back, which is nice.
